nd AI Governance\",\"description\":\"Cybersecurity executive, author, and international speaker specializing in AI, emerging technologies, and digital risk.\",\"sameAs\":[\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/arnaudwiehe\"],\"knowsAbout\":[\"AI Governance\",\"Cybersecurity\",\"Emerging Technologies\",\"Risk Management\",\"Digital Transformation\"],\"alumniOf\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"ISACA\"},\"hasCredential\":[{\"@type\":\"EducationalOccupationalCredential\",\"credentialCategory\":\"Certification\",\"name\":\"AIGP - Artificial Intelligence Governance Professional\"},{\"@type\":\"EducationalOccupationalCredential\",\"credentialCategory\":\"Certification\",\"name\":\"CISSP - Certified Information Systems Security Professional\"},{\"@type\":\"EducationalOccupationalCredential\",\"credentialCategory\":\"Certification\",\"name\":\"CCSP - Certified Cloud Security Professional\"},{\"@type\":\"EducationalOccupationalCredential\",\"credentialCategory\":\"Certification\",\"name\":\"CISM - Certified Information Security Manager\"},{\"@type\":\"EducationalOccupationalCredential\",\"credentialCategory\":\"Certification\",\"name\":\"CISA - Certified Information Systems Auditor\"},{\"@type\":\"EducationalOccupationalCredential\",\"credentialCategory\":\"Certification\",\"name\":\"CIPP/E - Certified Information Privacy Professional (Europe)\"}],\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Book\",\"name\":\"The Book on Cybersecurity\",\"url\":\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0C2SCKX7J\"},{\"@type\":\"Book\",\"name\":\"Emerging Tech, Emerging Threats\",\"url\":\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CXXL8W58\"}]}</script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/03~yq9q893hmn.js\" noModule=\"\"></script></head><body style=\"min-height:100vh\"><div hidden=\"\"><!--$--><!--/$--></div><nav class=\"nav-wrapper\"><div class=\"nav-inner\"><a class=\"nav-logo\" href=\"/\">Arnaud Wiehe</a><div class=\"nav-links\"><a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"/\">About</a><a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"/books\">Books</a><a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"/speaking\">Speaking</a><a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"/articles\">Writing</a><a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"/music\">Music</a><a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"/#contact\">Contact</a></div></div></nav><main class=\"articles-page\"><header class=\"articles-header\"><h1>Writing</h1><p class=\"subtitle\">Thoughts on AI governance, cybersecurity leadership, emerging technologies, and what I&#x27;m learning along the way.</p></header><div class=\"articles-list\"><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">April 8, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">Article</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">5 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/ncsc-vibe-coding-safeguards\">NCSC on Vibe Coding Safeguards: The Real Risk Is Control, Not Code</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">The NCSC&#x27;s clear signal to security leaders: AI-generated &quot;vibe coding&quot; is inevitable. The question isn&#x27;t whether to adopt it, but how to control it before it scales insecurity across your organization.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/ncsc-vibe-coding-safeguards\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">April 7, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">Article</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">5 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/ai-governance-journey\">The AI Governance Journey (It&#x27;s Not About a Checklist)</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">Stop treating AI governance like a spreadsheet exercise. Framework implementation is not a checklist—it is a transformation journey. And increasingly, it is a competitive differentiator.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/ai-governance-journey\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><a class=\"article-list-image-link\" href=\"/articles/iso-42001-compliance-final\"><div class=\"article-list-image-wrap\"><img src=\"/images/articles/iso-42001-compliance-final.jpg\" alt=\"ISO 42001 Compliance: A Practical Guide for AI Governance\" class=\"article-list-image\"/></div></a><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">April 4, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">AI Governance</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">6 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/iso-42001-compliance-final\">ISO 42001 Compliance: A Practical Guide for AI Governance</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">In December 2023, ISO/IEC 42001 became the world’s first certifiable AI management system standard. Here’s what it requires, how it relates to the EU AI Act and NIST AI RMF, and what boards should ask before pursuing certification.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/iso-42001-compliance-final\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">April 3, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">Cyber resilience</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">5 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/cyber-resilience-after-the-hype\">Cyber Resilience After the Hype: What &#x27;When Disaster Strikes&#x27; Means Today</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The second best time is now. In March 2024, a major cloud provider experienced a four-hour outage that cascaded through thousands of businesses worldwide. None of these organizations had been breached. Their problem was not prevention failure but resilience failure.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/cyber-resilience-after-the-hype\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">April 3, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">Board governance</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">5 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/third-party-cyber-risk-board-level\">Why Third-Party Cyber Risk Is Now a Board-Level Strategy Problem</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">A chain is only as strong as its weakest link, and modern organizations have thousands of links. In January 2024, a healthcare technology vendor suffered a ransomware attack that encrypted patient records for 450 hospitals across three countries. The hospitals themselves had robust security programs. None of it mattered. The attack came through a trusted vendor.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/third-party-cyber-risk-board-level\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">April 1, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">AI Security</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">6 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/owasp-top-10-agentic-ai\">The OWASP Top 10 for Agentic Applications</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">OWASP’s Top 10 for Agentic Applications is one of the clearest early frameworks for understanding how autonomous AI systems change the cybersecurity risk landscape. Here is why it matters for security leaders now.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/owasp-top-10-agentic-ai\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><a class=\"article-list-image-link\" href=\"/articles/ai-governance-cybersecurity\"><div class=\"article-list-image-wrap\"><img src=\"/images/articles/ai-governance-cybersecurity.svg\" alt=\"AI Governance Starts as Cybersecurity Governance\" class=\"article-list-image\"/></div></a><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">March 25, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">AI Governance</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">7 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/ai-governance-cybersecurity\">AI Governance Starts as Cybersecurity Governance</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">The good news is that effective AI governance does not require inventing entirely new frameworks. Organizations that have built robust cybersecurity governance already have the foundation. The challenge is extending those structures to address AI&#x27;s unique risks.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/ai-governance-cybersecurity\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><a class=\"article-list-image-link\" href=\"/articles/boards-cyber-agenda-2026\"><div class=\"article-list-image-wrap\"><img src=\"/images/articles/boards-cyber-agenda-2026.svg\" alt=\"The Board&#x27;s Cyber Agenda Has Changed: What Directors Need to Ask in 2026\" class=\"article-list-image\"/></div></a><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">March 25, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">Board Governance</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">8 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/boards-cyber-agenda-2026\">The Board&#x27;s Cyber Agenda Has Changed: What Directors Need to Ask in 2026</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">Something fundamental shifted in how boards must approach cybersecurity. Directors are now expected to understand cyber as a business resilience issue, a fiduciary responsibility, and increasingly, a personal liability concern. Here are the five questions that should now be standard in every boardroom.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/boards-cyber-agenda-2026\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><a class=\"article-list-image-link\" href=\"/articles/shadow-ai-guide-2026\"><div class=\"article-list-image-wrap\"><img src=\"/images/articles/shadow-ai-guide-2026.jpg\" alt=\"Shadow AI: What to Do in 2026\" class=\"article-list-image\"/></div></a><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">March 25, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">AI Governance</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">8 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/shadow-ai-guide-2026\">Shadow AI: What to Do in 2026</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">In 2023, Samsung employees inadvertently uploaded sensitive information to ChatGPT—becoming the most cited example of shadow AI. With 28% of employees now using unapproved AI tools at work, organizations need a Shadow AI Discovery and Response Programme. The EU AI Act now imposes fines up to €15 million for deploying high-risk AI without proper governance.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/shadow-ai-guide-2026\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">March 22, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">AI Governance</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">4 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/year-of-autonomous-agents\">The Year of Autonomous Agents</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">Autonomous agents change the security model fundamentally. Why 2026 feels like an inflection point for AI governance, accountability, and agent security.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/year-of-autonomous-agents\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">March 20, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">Cybersecurity</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">5 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/openclaw-security-crisis-5-cves-2026\">5 CVEs in 7 Days: The OpenClaw Security Crisis Is Here</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">The shift to agentic computing has begun, but security is still DIY. This week, five new vulnerabilities dropped for OpenClaw — five ways your AI agent can be turned against you. Just like early web commerce needed SSL and fraud protection to become mainstream, AI agents need security to achieve widespread adoption. Here&#x27;s why early adopters must roll their own security — and what that means for leaders deploying OpenClaw today.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/openclaw-security-crisis-5-cves-2026\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">March 18, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">Cybersecurity</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">5 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/openclaw-security-best-practices\">OpenClaw Security Best Practices: A Practical Guide</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">Practical security best practices for OpenClaw deployments. Learn how to harden your AI agent setup with actionable tips for credentials, network security, and configuration management.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/openclaw-security-best-practices\">Read article →</a></div></article><article class=\"article-list-card\"><div class=\"article-list-body\"><div class=\"article-meta\"><span class=\"article-date\">March 16, 2026</span><span class=\"article-category\">Industry Trends</span><span class=\"article-reading-time\">5 min read</span></div><h2><a class=\"article-link\" href=\"/articles/rise-of-openclaw\">The Rise of OpenClaw: Why AI Agents Are Taking Over</a></h2><p class=\"article-excerpt\">OpenClaw is the fastest-growing AI agent framework. Here&#x27;s why developers are flocking to it and what it means for the future of work, automation, and human-AI collaboration.</p><a class=\"read-more\" href=\"/articles/rise-of-openclaw\">Read article →</a></div></article></div><div class=\"newsletter-cta\"><h3>Get articles in your inbox</h3><p>Join the newsletter for weekly insights on AI leadership and emerging technology.</p><a href=\"mailto:arnaud@arnaudwiehe.com?subject=Newsletter Subscribe\" class=\"newsletter-button\">Subscribe →</a></div></main><!--$--><!--/$--><button class=\"mobile-nav-toggle \" aria-label=\"Open menu\" aria-expanded=\"false\"><span class=\"hamburger \"><span class=\"hamburger-line\"></span><span class=\"hamburger-line\"></span><span class=\"hamburger-line\"></span></span></button><div class=\"mobile-nav-overlay \"><nav class=\"mobile-nav\"><div class=\"mobile-nav-header\"><a class=\"mobile-nav-logo\" href=\"/\">Arnaud Wiehe</a></div><ul class=\"mobile-nav-links\"><li><a class=\"mobile-nav-link\" href=\"/\">About</a></li><li><a class=\"mobile-nav-link\" href=\"/speaking\">Speaking</a></li><li><a class=\"mobile-nav-link\" href=\"/articles\">Writing</a></li><li><a class=\"mobile-nav-link\" href=\"/books\">Books</a></li><li><a class=\"mobile-nav-link\" href=\"/music\">Music</a></li><li><a class=\"mobile-nav-link\" href=\"/#contact\">Contact</a></li></ul><div class=\"mobile-nav-footer\"><a href=\"mailto:arnaud@arnaudwiehe.com\" class=\"mobile-nav-email\">arnaud@arnaudwiehe.com</a><div class=\"mobile-nav-socials\"><a href=\"https://linkedin.com/in/arnaudwiehe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">LinkedIn</a></div></div></nav></div><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/15xrurgzs99gv.js\" id=\"_R_\" async=\"\"></script><script>(self.__next_f=self.__next_f||[]).push([0])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"1:\\\"$Sreact.fragment\\\"\\n3:I[12820,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0dzs3-e~z3uea.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0d3shmwh5_nmn.js\\\"],\\\"default\\\"]\\n4:I[39756,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0dzs3-e~z3uea.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0d3shmwh5_nmn.js\\\"],\\\"default\\\"]\\nc:I[68027,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0dzs3-e~z3uea.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0d3shmwh5_nmn.js\\\"],\\\"default\\\",1]\\n:HL[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0r~~u_wxwhoac.c